  "texts": [
    "Yet, other scholars like Piantadosi (2023) hold a contrasting view, positioning LLMs as genuine reflections of human linguistic cognition.",
    "Empirical studies have emerged as a crucial tool to answer this debate.",
    "Pioneering work by Binz and Schulz (2023) subjected GPT-3 to a battery of psychological tests, originally crafted to understand facets of human thought processes, ranging from decision-making matrices to reasoning pathways.",
    "The outcomes were intriguing, with GPT-3 not just mirroring but at times outperforming human benchmarks in specific scenarios.",
    "On a similar trajectory, Kosinski (2023) assessed the capacity of LLMs to understand and respond to false-belief scenarios, often utilized to gauge human empathy and comprehension."
  ],
